title: Hamid-ur-Rehman wins PK-08 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Hamid-ur-Rehman has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-8, Swat-VI by securing 33,152 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was PML-N candidate Jalat who bagged 15,007 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained at 34.05 per cent.
